ht|g|at|This is the unusual play of a smaller trump under the opponent's ruffing trump. The situation  occurs when there are no cards in both your hand and the right side defender other than trumps. The goal is to  leave this defender on lead, endplayed. This may not happen very frequently though worth being familiar with. 

Here are two example layouts where the underruff would be required:|
