ht|r|at|In a: At the end of a spade contract, you play the @hA from dummy. If East ruffs with the 8, you can overruff with the 9 for  two trump tricks. So East, having the exact layout of the trumps in mind, would instead ruff with the Jack. If you overruff now with the Ace, you will be endplayed and have to give East two trump tricks.  To assure yourself two trump tricks, you should play the 6 under the Jack, endplaying East.|
